$$&lt;p&gt;where&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Aâ‚–, Bâ‚– are Fourier coefficients, which indicate how much of each sine and cosine is needed to add up to recover f(x);&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;
&lt;p&gt;k stands for k-th frequency.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;
&lt;p&gt;When k=0, cos0=1, sin0=0, so there&amp;rsquo;s a constant Aâ‚€&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;
&lt;p&gt;These sine and cosine waves are 2Ï€ periodic.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
